00:17:55,035 --> 00:18:00,337
Metroidvanias are nice for that because they can have secrets and boss fights and that

266
00:18:00,377 --> 00:18:05,319
kind of thing, but I think puzzle games are even more suited for that because they can

267
00:18:05,379 --> 00:18:15,963
have like meta puzzles, they can have things where some simple idea is iterated in some

268
00:18:16,003 --> 00:18:18,204
way that the player doesn't expect at all.

269
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:23,051
And in Ba Ba Is You I kind of try to make every level, or as many levels as possible,

270
00:18:23,992 --> 00:18:31,413
do something new so that I would kind of maximize the amount of these kinds of surprising moments, surprising twists.

271
00:18:32,034 --> 00:18:36,675
That is something that I learned from the Stephen Sausage Roll and the Snake Bird games.

272
00:18:36,715 --> 00:18:46,277
Those games both kind of do a really good job at requiring you to do something at least slightly unique.

273
00:18:47,554 --> 00:18:53,338
in every level and that is something I kind of strove for and that I find

274
00:18:53,458 --> 00:18:57,000
enjoying enjoyable when I play puzzle games myself and I'm actually kind of

275
00:18:57,801 --> 00:19:01,083
trying to always trying to find more puzzle games that follow a similar

