281
00:19:21,850 --> 00:19:23,471
is that if something is shut,

282
00:19:24,191 --> 00:19:25,791
if it touches something that is open,

283
00:19:25,971 --> 00:19:27,572
they destroy each other.

284
00:19:27,812 --> 00:19:29,352
And saying like, if something is open,

285
00:19:29,512 --> 00:19:32,233
if a door is open and it touches a key that is shut,

286
00:19:32,673 --> 00:19:33,713
they destroy each other.

287
00:19:34,454 --> 00:19:36,774
But obviously, for a very obvious reason,

288
00:19:36,994 --> 00:19:38,875
if the game says door is shut,

289
00:19:39,335 --> 00:19:43,216
people assume that the door is like a solid object,

290
00:19:43,236 --> 00:19:44,256
that you cannot move through it.

291
00:19:44,756 --> 00:19:46,117
But that is not actually true.

292
00:19:46,654 --> 00:19:54,084
And the reason why breaking the rule, door is shut, didn't let you pass through the door is because there is also a door is stop at the top.

293
00:19:54,765 --> 00:19:57,508
And that level causes a lot of trouble.

294
00:19:57,969 --> 00:20:02,775
And I feel that it's kind of a, at least to some extent, it's a failure from my kind of tutorializing.

295
00:20:03,187 --> 00:20:04,428
I just kind of wanted to point it out.

296
00:20:04,708 --> 00:20:07,890
That's interesting because from a subconscious perspective, my brain was already tracking

297
00:20:07,910 --> 00:20:10,131
towards if I change what the door is, I can get through the door.

298
00:20:10,311 --> 00:20:11,391
Sorry, Alex, I jumped on you there.

299
00:20:11,731 --> 00:20:13,532
No, not at all.

300
00:20:13,732 --> 00:20:17,114
And that's it's interesting to hear you describe that problem, because I did sense it as I

301
00:20:17,174 --> 00:20:21,256
ran through it, because I got confused why killing doors stopped didn't do anything.

302
00:20:21,576 --> 00:20:25,798
But then it just sort of thankfully my brain just subverted or moved to the next problem

303
00:20:25,838 --> 00:20:28,679
solving technique, which, you know, like I was testing a hypothesis, right?

304
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:31,481
Like this game is very hypothesis. If I try this, then this will happen.

305
00:20:31,881 --> 00:20:41,846
and thankfully that just let me try something different. Nope, wall is defeat. God damn it.

306
00:20:41,866 --> 00:20:45,908
Yeah, someone pointed, like a player pointed out at some point that I should have made the word

307
00:20:46,808 --> 00:20:54,352
open should be unlock and shut should be locked and I agree. It would be maybe a bit more

308
00:20:54,452 --> 00:20:56,673
informative or like more intuitive.

309
00:20:58,506 --> 00:21:02,354
There's actually a pretty interesting story, I'm getting sidetracked, but there's the word

310
00:21:02,555 --> 00:21:07,686
DEFEAT, and in the original game jam version of the game, the word was actually KILLED.

311
00:21:08,292 --> 00:21:13,133
But because the game is so cutesy, and I also kinda, despite developing a Metroidvania,

312
00:21:13,193 --> 00:21:18,595
I generally prefer having, like, non-violence in my games.

313
00:21:18,675 --> 00:21:22,135
I try to find and figure out solutions that are less violent if possible.

314
00:21:22,515 --> 00:21:27,117
So I felt kill was a very violent word, especially, like, if you see, here's Baba.

315
00:21:27,257 --> 00:21:29,237
Baba is killed. That's brutal.

316
00:21:30,097 --> 00:21:34,078
And I spent, in the end, I think like a half a year

317
00:21:35,178 --> 00:21:37,999
trying to figure out what to change the word kill to.

318
00:21:38,943 --> 00:21:43,945
And because the idea is that kill only destroys something that is you.

319
00:21:44,165 --> 00:21:46,266
It doesn't harm anything else but you.

320
00:21:46,706 --> 00:21:50,567
So the idea is that it's harmful to living things, so to say.

321
00:21:51,448 --> 00:21:54,869
And kill conveys that idea really well.

322
00:21:55,309 --> 00:21:59,971
And I think, like, after trying many ideas and getting suggestions from people,

323
00:22:00,391 --> 00:22:03,552
defeat was the, like, next best answer.

324
00:22:03,692 --> 00:22:05,732
There was, like, gone and poof and...

325
00:22:07,201 --> 00:22:11,184
I don't remember the others, but there were several suggestions we went through.

326
00:22:11,204 --> 00:22:13,406
It was an interesting problem.

327
00:22:13,486 --> 00:22:15,708
