347
00:23:28,006 --> 00:23:29,967
But the reason...

348
00:23:31,167 --> 00:23:32,007
The kind of...

349
00:23:33,708 --> 00:23:39,549
If we discount this specific situation where something that would be useful

350
00:23:40,150 --> 00:23:44,131
is maybe not taught by the game if you skip these levels...

351
00:23:46,035 --> 00:23:53,541
I wanted to make it so that you always have as many options as possible for kind of progressing

352
00:23:54,182 --> 00:23:58,425
because in a puzzle game it's very easy to get mentally stuck.

353
00:24:00,867 --> 00:24:06,932
And kind of if you only have one option for a puzzle if you get stuck in that puzzle it might

354
00:24:06,972 --> 00:24:14,598
be that you kind of you won't get anywhere because you are stuck trying a single idea.

355
00:24:15,091 --> 00:24:20,334
over and over and not kind of refreshing your mind. You need to take a break to kind of refresh

356
00:24:20,374 --> 00:24:29,778
your concept on what you are doing and the offering the players multiple options to pick from

357
00:24:30,359 --> 00:24:35,701
I feel is nicer because if they get stuck in one puzzle they still can do something in the game.

358
00:24:35,741 --> 00:24:41,124
They don't have to close the game and wait until they get the insight. They can go to other level

359
00:24:41,364 --> 00:24:42,465
which might be easier for them.

360
00:24:43,774 --> 00:24:49,919
Another reason is that in Baba Is You I felt that it would be best if the levels were grouped

361
00:24:50,319 --> 00:24:56,205
by the words used in them instead of by, like, purely by difficulty.

362
00:24:56,285 --> 00:25:01,609
Obviously there needs to be, like, a difficulty curve, but especially because some of the

363
00:25:01,669 --> 00:25:06,313
specific words are very... odd, so to say.

364
00:25:06,333 --> 00:25:08,995
Like, very complex, very specific.

365
00:25:11,163 --> 00:25:15,766
I felt that it would be nicer if the player doesn't have to learn so many words at once,

366
00:25:16,306 --> 00:25:19,848
but instead different areas would have different words.

367
00:25:20,488 --> 00:25:28,672
And if I group the levels using that criteria, there will inevitably be levels that are easier

368
00:25:29,713 --> 00:25:33,014
in one area than there were some levels in the earlier areas.

369
00:25:33,214 --> 00:25:37,476
Like if I introduce a new word entirely, a new concept.

370
00:25:38,376 --> 00:25:41,920
I need to make an easy level that tutorializes that concept.

371
00:25:42,762 --> 00:25:49,551
And so I thought it would be odd if the player kind of expects...

372
00:25:51,647 --> 00:25:57,148
an even difficulty curve and then gets into a new area and they're like, hey, this is a super easy level.

373
00:25:57,668 --> 00:26:05,290
So I decided to go with the concept that every area kind of resets the difficulty curve at least a little bit, like pushes it back.

374
00:26:05,930 --> 00:26:10,891
So in every area you can start from the easy levels, you can beat the easy levels and move on,

375
00:26:11,531 --> 00:26:18,913
but if you want you can keep going for the harder levels that like really explore the limits of the words introduced in those worlds.

376
00:26:19,670 --> 00:26:31,518
And this is partially also related to how, because I knew that the game would be possibly pretty difficult.

377
00:26:31,819 --> 00:26:38,644
It's very hard to estimate as a game developer how difficult a game is by yourself,

378
00:26:39,224 --> 00:26:40,925
but I assumed that the game would be pretty difficult.

379
00:26:41,125 --> 00:26:46,089
But I knew that there would be people who like to play these kinds of games.

380
00:26:46,615 --> 00:26:52,920
or them there that would like to see like BABA in action, even if they don't enjoy playing super hard puzzle games.

381
00:26:53,540 --> 00:26:59,886
I wanted to have a system where they, or actually a tester suggested having a system for kind of opting out

382
00:27:00,526 --> 00:27:07,132
once you have seen enough, so that people who want to see the system but don't want to get super hardcore on it,

383
00:27:07,912 --> 00:27:08,593
they can play the game.

384
00:27:09,367 --> 00:27:13,747
they get offered some, like, hey, if you beat this level, you can say that you beat the game

385
00:27:14,368 --> 00:27:18,028
and you can move on, you don't have to get stressed and annoyed about the difficulty.

